1
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:31,760
Wait for me.

2
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:33,039
I can't keep up.

3
00:01:52,070 --> 00:01:53,600
How did this plane get here?

4
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:55,250
Do you think it crashed?

5
00:01:55,509 --> 00:01:56,710
Don't talk nonsense.

6
00:01:56,740 --> 00:01:58,759
If a plane fell from the sky,

7
00:01:58,870 --> 00:02:00,350
it'd be in pieces.

8
00:02:00,370 --> 00:02:00,920
From now on,

9
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:02,560
this is our secret base.

10
00:02:02,620 --> 00:02:03,870
Don't tell anyone.

11
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:05,320
Come on. Let's go take a look.

12
00:02:05,320 --> 00:02:05,850
Let's go.

13
00:03:45,870 --> 00:03:50,310
[THE GUILTY]

14
00:03:50,750 --> 00:03:54,990
[Episode 2]

15
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:58,150
[Lighthouse at Nanping Port Dock]

16
00:03:58,150 --> 00:04:01,470
Officer Qin, I need to step out.

17
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:34,250
Where is Lu Ming?

18
00:04:36,670 --> 00:04:37,720
Is Lu Ming here?

19
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,920
Is Shanshan here?

20
00:04:57,860 --> 00:04:58,980
When I got there,

21
00:04:59,590 --> 00:05:01,120
Shanshan was already gone.

22
00:05:06,030 --> 00:05:07,890
Did you really kill Wang Bingkun?

23
00:05:13,620 --> 00:05:14,620
I didn't kill him.

24
00:05:16,270 --> 00:05:17,390
When I arrived,

25
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:18,780
he was already dead.

26
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:37,260
The police got a photo of you.

27
00:05:38,490 --> 00:05:39,890
It was taken from behind.

28
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:46,260
I suspect Shanshan's disappearance

29
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:48,810
has something to do with Ma Derong.

30
00:05:50,110 --> 00:05:52,070
If Ma Derong wanted the child,

31
00:05:52,090 --> 00:05:53,830
why go through all this trouble?

32
00:05:53,830 --> 00:05:55,890
He could've just come and asked for her.

33
00:05:55,890 --> 00:05:57,440
But I found a lot of photos

34
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,720
of Shanshan in Ma Derong's room.

35
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:02,630
While I was sorting through those photos,

36
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:04,140
I spotted someone.

37
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:05,690
It was Wang Bingkun.

38
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:08,620
And now that Shanshan is missing,

39
00:06:08,750 --> 00:06:10,150
Ma Derong is missing too.

40
00:06:11,760 --> 00:06:12,970
You mean

41
00:06:14,510 --> 00:06:16,270
Ma Derong killed Wang Bingkun

42
00:06:17,110 --> 00:06:18,710
and then took Shanshan away?

43
00:06:20,270 --> 00:06:21,800
Then who sent Wang Bingkun?

44
00:06:25,100 --> 00:06:26,690
I'll look into it later.

45
00:06:27,310 --> 00:06:29,110
But we have a bigger problem now.

46
00:06:30,310 --> 00:06:32,770
The police are investigating Hou Shanshan.

47
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,480
If they keep digging,

48
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:38,880
they will find out
what happened back then.

49
00:06:41,570 --> 00:06:42,480
Are we really not going to see

50
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:43,950
Shanshan turn 18?

51
00:06:45,810 --> 00:06:47,010
We can't let Shanshan

52
00:06:47,159 --> 00:06:48,760
pay for the mistakes we made.

53
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:51,140
So we have to find her before

54
00:06:51,430 --> 00:06:52,630
we turn ourselves in.

55
00:07:16,650 --> 00:07:25,280
[1999]

56
00:07:36,350 --> 00:07:37,350
Sorry, excuse me.

57
00:07:41,850 --> 00:07:43,520
Excuse me. Thank you.

58
00:07:50,870 --> 00:07:56,590
[No Dangerous Goods Allowed]

59
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,409
Why are you here?

60
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:01,920
Didn't you say you were going
to the dining car?

61
00:08:03,570 --> 00:08:05,630
[No Dangerous Goods Allowed]

62
00:08:05,630 --> 00:08:07,920
It's quite comfortable here, isn't it?

63
00:08:10,030 --> 00:08:11,360
Then I'll stay here too.

64
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:12,040
You shouldn't stay here.

65
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:12,920
Just go back.

66
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:14,240
I...

67
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:15,950
Didn't you say it's comfortable here?

68
00:08:15,950 --> 00:08:17,750
We have to stand for hours here.

69
00:08:17,750 --> 00:08:19,360
Did we buy these tickets for nothing?

70
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,480
I'm not going back.

71
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:21,560
Be good.

72
00:08:22,540 --> 00:08:23,140
No.

73
00:08:23,140 --> 00:08:26,660
[No Dangerous Goods Allowed]

74
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,120
What?

75
00:08:33,610 --> 00:08:37,150
♪ Dispel the melancholy in my heart ♪

76
00:08:38,650 --> 00:08:42,450
♪ We talk and laugh, as if our souls
have long been familiar ♪

77
00:08:43,539 --> 00:08:47,490
♪ But my heart skips a beat,
I'm lost in this dream of youth ♪

78
00:08:48,870 --> 00:08:53,070
♪ Oh, my first love,
I tremble inside as I plead ♪

79
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:54,970
This way.

80
00:08:54,970 --> 00:08:56,320
♪ Are you the one
who belongs only to me? ♪

81
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:56,910
Please watch your step.

82
00:08:56,910 --> 00:08:58,510
Everyone, please stay safe.

83
00:08:58,910 --> 00:09:00,180
Hold on to your tickets.

84
00:09:00,180 --> 00:09:00,240
♪ I'm afraid to say it,
and afraid you'll know ♪

85
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:01,120
Be careful.

86
00:09:04,830 --> 00:09:08,020
♪ I just hope you'll catch me
if I gather the courage to run to you ♪

87
00:09:08,020 --> 00:09:11,120
[Exit]

88
00:09:11,170 --> 00:09:16,750
[Nanping Station:
Have a Safe and Pleasant Trip]

89
00:09:16,750 --> 00:09:18,320
Do you think Lin Hua
will come to pick us up?

90
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:20,000
Where is he?

91
00:09:32,150 --> 00:09:33,610
Everyone's looking at us.

92
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:40,670
Lin Hua!

93
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:47,280
You're finally back.

94
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:48,600
Why are you still so skinny?

95
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:49,910
Is the food that bad?

96
00:09:49,910 --> 00:09:50,840
Not really.

97
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:52,520
Why do you look so tanned?

98
00:09:52,630 --> 00:09:53,750
To make you two look paler.

99
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:55,120
I got this tan just for you.

100
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:56,240
You've got a way with words now.

101
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:57,360
-Give it to me.
-It's okay.

102
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:58,120
Come on, give it to me.

103
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:59,030
It's okay.

104
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,720
You've been working out.

105
00:10:00,790 --> 00:10:01,600
Come on.

106
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:02,670
I'm Bruce Lee.

107
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:03,240
Fine.

108
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:04,900
I'll give you a chance to show off.

109
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:05,630
Give it to me.

110
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:09,670
They're demolishing everything?

111
00:10:09,670 --> 00:10:10,790
Yeah, all of it.

112
00:10:11,030 --> 00:10:13,240
They're gonna build some kind of BD.

113
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:15,080
BD? What BD?

114
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:16,510
It's CBD.

115
00:10:16,510 --> 00:10:17,960
Right, right, that BD.

116
00:10:20,390 --> 00:10:21,440
Only two years till graduation.

117
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:22,720
What are your plans?

118
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:24,870
Either Shanghai or Beijing.

119
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:27,000
Why only those two?

120
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,120
You're not even considering Nanping?

121
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:29,120
We're gonna build a BD here.

122
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:31,000
You two could make it anywhere.

123
00:10:31,390 --> 00:10:32,510
Don't listen to his nonsense.

124
00:10:32,510 --> 00:10:33,600
We've already decided.

125
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:35,440
We'll come back.
So we can stay close to you

126
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:36,600
and our parents.

127
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:37,600
Really?

128
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:39,840
Mark my words.

129
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:41,040
You two are going to be

130
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:43,080
Nanping's richest people someday.

131
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:46,600
Fine. Once we become Nanping's richest,

132
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:50,000
I'll get you a proper car.

133
00:10:53,070 --> 00:10:54,030
You promised.

134
00:10:54,030 --> 00:10:54,600
Keep your word,

135
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:55,440
no backing out.

136
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:56,550
Of course.

137
00:10:56,870 --> 00:10:58,200
I'm not trying to rip you off,

138
00:10:58,200 --> 00:10:59,510
but you have to buy me an automatic.

139
00:10:59,510 --> 00:11:00,750
After all, I can only handle

140
00:11:00,750 --> 00:11:02,160
the fancy cars.

141
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:06,440
Lin Hua, what happened to your leg?

142
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:08,400
It's nothing.

143
00:11:08,870 --> 00:11:10,670
Why are there so many burn scars?

144
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:16,150
I got them from working at the factory.

145
00:11:16,220 --> 00:11:17,960
What kind of work would do that?

146
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:19,240
Did someone bully you or something?

147
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:20,970
Who would bully me?

148
00:11:21,670 --> 00:11:24,390
It was just a work accident. It's nothing.

149
00:11:29,390 --> 00:11:30,360
Alright.

150
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:31,750
We're here.

151
00:11:35,550 --> 00:11:36,630
Xia Xue,

152
00:11:36,630 --> 00:11:37,510
you go up first.

153
00:11:37,510 --> 00:11:39,110
Lin Hua and I will be right up.

154
00:11:40,270 --> 00:11:41,130
Are you scared?

155
00:11:41,670 --> 00:11:42,530
Are you scared?

156
00:11:42,630 --> 00:11:44,030
What would I be scared of?

157
00:11:44,790 --> 00:11:45,390
Fine.

158
00:11:46,270 --> 00:11:47,200
You said it.

159
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:50,130
See you tonight.

160
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,390
We haven't picked up our luggage yet.

161
00:11:52,390 --> 00:11:53,720
It's fine. I'll bring it to you later.

162
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:55,120
Seeing Uncle Xia comes first.

163
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:56,240
Hope you're still alive tonight.

164
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:56,790
Goodbye.

165
00:11:56,790 --> 00:11:57,720
Good luck.

166
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:01,480
I knew those two
would get together eventually.

167
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,000
Uncle Niu.

168
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:02,750
You think you know everything.

169
00:12:02,750 --> 00:12:03,650
Auntie Yang.

170
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:05,540
Xue, you're back.

171
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:07,590
Xue, You're about to graduate, right?

172
00:12:07,590 --> 00:12:08,870
Xue, you're back.

173
00:12:10,470 --> 00:12:11,230
Wait.

174
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:13,320
Are we really going to see your dad?

175
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:14,790
I thought you weren't afraid.

176
00:12:14,790 --> 00:12:15,750
I'm not.

177
00:12:15,750 --> 00:12:16,840
Then let's go.

178
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:19,480
But I'm not mentally prepared yet.

179
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:20,390
Prepared for what?

180
00:12:20,390 --> 00:12:21,320
I...

181
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:23,150
I just need to get ready.

182
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:25,240
Lu Ming.

183
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:25,750
Not you. Xue.

184
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:27,010
Pour Uncle Xia a drink.

185
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:28,000
Uncle Xia.

186
00:12:29,030 --> 00:12:29,870
Try this.

187
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:32,970
-I made this for you today.
-Thank you.

188
00:12:34,150 --> 00:12:34,750
Uncle Xia.

189
00:12:35,030 --> 00:12:36,630
I'd like to offer you a toast.

190
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:39,960
A toast's supposed to

191
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:41,360
have a reason.

192
00:12:42,130 --> 00:12:44,560
What's yours for?

193
00:12:46,150 --> 00:12:47,750
This is a welcome toast for me.

194
00:12:47,750 --> 00:12:49,080
Right. A welcome toast.

195
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,510
This isn't a welcome toast.

196
00:12:50,510 --> 00:12:52,270
I was at work today

197
00:12:52,270 --> 00:12:55,200
when I heard someone
ran off with my daughter.

198
00:12:56,270 --> 00:12:58,120
If you don't explain this clearly,

199
00:12:58,120 --> 00:12:59,030
we're not done.

200
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:01,840
Xia Gang.

201
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:04,390
The kids are grown up.

202
00:13:04,390 --> 00:13:06,200
Stop doing this old-fashioned

203
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,790
arranged marriage thing.

204
00:13:07,790 --> 00:13:08,600
What?

205
00:13:09,650 --> 00:13:11,580
You're saying I'm old-fashioned?

206
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:13,260
Alright, alright.

207
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:16,080
You two always bicker
in front of the kids.

208
00:13:16,510 --> 00:13:18,030
This old habit of yours

209
00:13:18,030 --> 00:13:20,550
-hasn't changed in all these years.
-What's the story
between my dad and yours?

210
00:13:20,550 --> 00:13:21,880
They always play chess,

211
00:13:21,910 --> 00:13:23,320
and my dad always takes back his moves.

212
00:13:23,320 --> 00:13:24,510
We've been neighbors for so many years,

213
00:13:24,510 --> 00:13:27,020
and we've always treated Xue
like our own daughter.

214
00:13:27,020 --> 00:13:28,020
Don't worry.

215
00:13:28,050 --> 00:13:29,790
When Xue marries into our family,

216
00:13:29,790 --> 00:13:31,630
we'll make sure she doesn't suffer a bit.

217
00:13:31,630 --> 00:13:32,510
Exactly.

218
00:13:34,630 --> 00:13:36,190
It doesn't matter what you two say.

219
00:13:36,190 --> 00:13:36,990
Uncle Xia,

220
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:37,930
don't worry.

221
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:39,630
I promise I'll treat Xia Xue well.

222
00:13:39,630 --> 00:13:40,690
Easy for you to say.

223
00:13:41,870 --> 00:13:43,320
How are you going
to take care of her?

224
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:44,630
I'm graduating from college soon.

225
00:13:44,630 --> 00:13:46,510
I'll find a good job after graduation.

226
00:13:46,510 --> 00:13:47,670
Then I'll work hard every day,

227
00:13:47,670 --> 00:13:49,080
and give the best things in the world

228
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:49,870
to Xia Xue.

229
00:13:50,330 --> 00:13:52,540
Yes, we'll work hard together.

230
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:03,930
I don't know what you see in him.

231
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:07,530
Lu Ming.

232
00:14:12,870 --> 00:14:14,670
Xue's mother passed away early,

233
00:14:14,990 --> 00:14:17,260
and I'm not good at taking care of people.

234
00:14:17,550 --> 00:14:20,670
I didn't really show her
much love growing up.

235
00:14:21,900 --> 00:14:24,900
Today, I'm entrusting Xue to you.

236
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:28,020
Just love her with all your heart

237
00:14:28,020 --> 00:14:29,810
and take care of her.

238
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:32,430
I promise.

239
00:14:35,460 --> 00:14:36,390
Drink slowly.

240
00:14:36,410 --> 00:14:37,040
Don't drink too much.

241
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:38,360
Come on, let's drink together.

242
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:39,150
Come on, Xia.

243
00:14:39,150 --> 00:14:40,360
-Come on.
-Come on.

244
00:14:40,870 --> 00:14:42,000
To the children.

245
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,200
I wish you happiness.

246
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:01,900
Hurry up.

247
00:15:02,510 --> 00:15:04,000
Does it sound like that old song?

248
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:04,550
It does.

249
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:07,290
Business is really good here.

250
00:15:07,290 --> 00:15:08,690
The grilling is too slow.

251
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,390
Is this place new?

252
00:15:11,630 --> 00:15:13,240
It's been open for a few months.

253
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:14,960
When it opened, I figured I'd wait

254
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:16,390
for you two's summer break

255
00:15:16,390 --> 00:15:18,520
and bring you here for a welcome treat.

256
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:21,320
People who make their own money
have more confidence.

257
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:22,260
Of course.

258
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:23,630
I'm way more mature

259
00:15:23,630 --> 00:15:25,000
than you students.

260
00:15:26,270 --> 00:15:26,870
Hey,

261
00:15:26,870 --> 00:15:28,550
I'm actually a bit older than you.

262
00:15:28,550 --> 00:15:30,550
So don't act like a big brother to me.

263
00:15:38,780 --> 00:15:39,380
Lin Hua.

264
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,730
This is a small gift Xia Xue and I

265
00:15:41,900 --> 00:15:43,670
specially picked out for you.

266
00:15:47,910 --> 00:15:49,230
You got me a gift?

267
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:50,750
Of course.

268
00:15:51,560 --> 00:15:53,240
Then I take back what I just said.

269
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:54,700
You two are indeed mature.

270
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:58,650
What is this?

271
00:15:59,510 --> 00:16:00,840
Is it for self-defense?

272
00:16:02,870 --> 00:16:04,280
It's a trekking pole. Look.

273
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:05,330
It's telescopic.

274
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:06,960
You can adjust it
to the angle that suits you.

275
00:16:06,960 --> 00:16:08,760
Everyone uses this for hiking now.

276
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:10,080
I've seen it on TV.

277
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:11,750
Then I have to go hiking.

278
00:16:11,750 --> 00:16:12,670
I have to use it.

279
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:13,980
You better train well.

280
00:16:14,270 --> 00:16:14,950
One day,

281
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:17,260
we'll go to Mount Everest together.

282
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:18,690
Forget Everest for now.

283
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:21,080
We can start with Lover's Peak.

284
00:16:21,100 --> 00:16:22,410
Sure, pick a date.

285
00:16:22,510 --> 00:16:23,080
We can go together.

286
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:23,630
Okay.

287
00:16:23,650 --> 00:16:24,530
Come on.

288
00:16:24,610 --> 00:16:25,200
Thank you.

289
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:26,030
-Here.
-Thank you.

290
00:16:26,030 --> 00:16:26,510
Cheers.

291
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:30,030
Xia Xue.

292
00:16:30,750 --> 00:16:32,900
This is the song you often sing.

293
00:16:34,510 --> 00:16:35,490
Then I'll go sing it.

294
00:16:35,490 --> 00:16:36,090
Come on.

295
00:16:36,550 --> 00:16:37,330
I'll go too.

296
00:16:43,790 --> 00:16:48,120
Rose, rose, the fairest of all.

297
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:52,550
Rose, rose, the brightest of all.

298
00:16:52,550 --> 00:16:56,750
Blooming on the branches
in endless summer.

299
00:16:56,750 --> 00:17:01,010
Rose, Rose, I love you.

300
00:17:01,150 --> 00:17:05,400
A heart's vow, a love so true.

301
00:17:05,680 --> 00:17:09,750
Holy light shines upon the earth.

302
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:12,270
Lin Hua.

303
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:14,329
Are these your friends?

304
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:16,510
Young Mr. Ma.

305
00:17:18,349 --> 00:17:19,920
Mr. Ma's asking you.

306
00:17:20,030 --> 00:17:20,720
Answer him.

307
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:21,839
Well sung!

308
00:17:23,750 --> 00:17:26,750
Mr. Ma is talking to you. Speak up.

309
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:31,810
Young Mr. Ma, these two are my friends.

310
00:17:32,430 --> 00:17:33,890
You just sang really well.

311
00:17:34,270 --> 00:17:36,200
I don't think I've seen you before.

312
00:17:36,350 --> 00:17:36,810
Come on.

313
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:39,980
Let's have a drink.

314
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:41,590
I...

315
00:17:42,730 --> 00:17:43,760
I don't know you.

316
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:46,060
I don't drink with strangers.

317
00:17:46,070 --> 00:17:48,350
We won't be strangers after a drink.

318
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:52,190
Young Mr. Ma. I'll drink with you for her.

319
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:54,240
It's none of your business.

320
00:17:56,510 --> 00:17:57,910
Let me introduce myself.

321
00:17:58,920 --> 00:17:59,940
I'm Ma Kai,

322
00:18:00,270 --> 00:18:03,030
the general manager of Nanping Shipyard.

323
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:06,680
Basically, I'm Lin Hua's boss.

324
00:18:06,680 --> 00:18:07,550
Right, Lin Hua?

325
00:18:07,550 --> 00:18:08,270
Yes, yes.

326
00:18:10,790 --> 00:18:13,110
If anyone in your family
works at the shipyard,

327
00:18:13,110 --> 00:18:14,710
my name carries some weight.

328
00:18:24,690 --> 00:18:25,690
Young Mr. Ma.

329
00:18:25,720 --> 00:18:27,590
My friend really can't hold her drink.

330
00:18:27,590 --> 00:18:28,580
Let me drink instead.

331
00:18:28,580 --> 00:18:30,070
Here's a toast to you.

332
00:18:30,070 --> 00:18:31,330
What's wrong, Lin Hua?

333
00:18:32,170 --> 00:18:34,300
You think that crutch makes you tough?

334
00:18:34,420 --> 00:18:36,340
Why would Kai drink with you?

335
00:18:36,550 --> 00:18:37,280
Why would...

336
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:39,680
Let go.

337
00:18:40,510 --> 00:18:40,830
It's okay.

338
00:18:40,830 --> 00:18:41,640
Let go.

339
00:18:42,030 --> 00:18:42,550
Let go.

340
00:18:42,780 --> 00:18:43,780
Alright. Lu Ming.

341
00:18:47,950 --> 00:18:48,750
If you mess up the stall,

342
00:18:48,750 --> 00:18:50,210
then what are we gonna eat?

343
00:18:54,330 --> 00:18:55,810
It's okay.

344
00:18:56,920 --> 00:18:58,030
It's so hot today.

345
00:18:58,030 --> 00:18:59,440
Try not to get so heated.

346
00:19:02,350 --> 00:19:03,270
This is on me.

347
00:19:04,510 --> 00:19:05,030
Lin Hua.

348
00:19:09,550 --> 00:19:10,280
Young Mr. Ma.

349
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:13,810
Later,

350
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:17,830
get this friend of yours
to come drink with me.

351
00:19:19,980 --> 00:19:22,040
Your leg's looking much better, huh?

352
00:19:26,470 --> 00:19:27,330
Ma Kai, right?

353
00:19:31,250 --> 00:19:33,850
You're the one who burned
Lin Hua's leg, right?

354
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:37,350
His leg's injured,

355
00:19:38,060 --> 00:19:40,970
so I was just testing if he could feel it.

356
00:19:41,810 --> 00:19:43,420
What, do you have a problem with that?

357
00:19:43,420 --> 00:19:44,650
You're going too far.

358
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:51,400
Sorry, Mr. Ma.

359
00:19:51,510 --> 00:19:52,800
Xia Xue, what are you doing?

360
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:54,030
-Mr. Ma, sorry.
-Are you alright, Kai?

361
00:19:54,030 --> 00:19:54,790
Get tissues.

362
00:19:54,810 --> 00:19:55,940
Hurry, get tissues.

363
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:56,720
Are you okay, Kai?

364
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:57,720
Sorry, I'm sorry.

365
00:20:01,750 --> 00:20:02,720
-Kai!
-Kai!

366
00:20:02,720 --> 00:20:03,750
Kai, are you okay?

367
00:20:03,750 --> 00:20:04,510
Hit him!

368
00:20:12,050 --> 00:20:14,480
Wu, give everyone the update.

369
00:20:16,310 --> 00:20:16,470
The kidnapping case has now
escalated into a homicide.

370
00:20:16,470 --> 00:20:19,550
[2010]

371
00:20:19,550 --> 00:20:20,830
Everyone is following standard procedures

372
00:20:20,830 --> 00:20:22,880
to look for the culprit and the hostages.

373
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:26,110
We asked Hou Shanshan's parents
about Wang Bingkun

374
00:20:26,350 --> 00:20:28,550
and the person captured
in the surveillance footage,

375
00:20:28,550 --> 00:20:30,550
and both said they didn't know them.

376
00:20:30,950 --> 00:20:31,160
[Couple]

377
00:20:31,160 --> 00:20:33,240
We've also gone through Hou Jun

378
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:34,640
and Xia Xue's social circles

379
00:20:34,640 --> 00:20:36,550
and haven't found
any suspicious leads so far.

380
00:20:36,550 --> 00:20:39,080
Since Hou Shanshan
is an illegitimate child,

381
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:39,200
[Wang Bingkun's Murder Case]

382
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:40,440
we also inquired about

383
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:41,880
the child's background.

384
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:44,030
Who is the child's biological father?

385
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:46,660
This is her privacy, isn't it?

386
00:20:47,070 --> 00:20:49,590
Xia Xue's dodging and Hou Jun's silence

387
00:20:49,590 --> 00:20:49,640
caught our attention,

388
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:51,070
[Hou Jun] [Couple] [Xia Xue]

389
00:20:51,070 --> 00:20:52,130
so I looked into it.

390
00:20:52,440 --> 00:20:54,720
Before marrying Hou Jun,

391
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:56,400
Xia Xue had a boyfriend—

392
00:20:57,110 --> 00:20:57,590
Lu Ming.

393
00:20:58,110 --> 00:20:58,750
Both of them

394
00:20:58,750 --> 00:21:00,470
were children of
Nanping Shipyard employees

395
00:21:00,470 --> 00:21:02,070
and were basically childhood sweethearts.

396
00:21:02,070 --> 00:21:03,830
They even got into
Huacheng University together.

397
00:21:03,830 --> 00:21:05,830
They also had a close mutual friend,

398
00:21:06,350 --> 00:21:07,110
Lin Hua.

399
00:21:09,480 --> 00:21:11,000
After failing the college entrance exam,

400
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:12,680
Lin Hua got a job at Nanping Shipyard.

401
00:21:12,680 --> 00:21:14,910
Everyone in the
shipyard's residential area

402
00:21:14,910 --> 00:21:17,590
knew about Lu Ming
and Xia Xue's relationship.

403
00:21:17,980 --> 00:21:20,240
Everyone considered them a perfect match.

404
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:21,260
However, for reasons unknown,

405
00:21:21,260 --> 00:21:22,070
they broke up

406
00:21:22,070 --> 00:21:23,070
ten years ago.

407
00:21:23,720 --> 00:21:24,590
Ten years ago?

408
00:21:24,640 --> 00:21:25,070
Yes.

409
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:29,480
Hou Shanshan just
turned ten this year, right?

410
00:21:30,270 --> 00:21:32,240
So Hou Shanshan's biological father

411
00:21:32,240 --> 00:21:33,350
could be Lu Ming.

412
00:21:35,070 --> 00:21:37,930
Judging from their relationship
and the timeline,

413
00:21:38,030 --> 00:21:39,290
it seems quite likely.

414
00:21:39,470 --> 00:21:40,320
By the way,

415
00:21:41,110 --> 00:21:42,160
Lu Ming is now the owner

416
00:21:42,160 --> 00:21:44,650
of Sancheng Financial Services.

417
00:21:46,070 --> 00:21:47,550
Such a good college student.

418
00:21:47,550 --> 00:21:49,540
What happened ten years ago?

419
00:21:54,430 --> 00:21:55,840
[Police Office Operating Procedures]

420
00:21:55,840 --> 00:21:57,500
You're all from the shipyard?

421
00:21:57,710 --> 00:21:58,950
Yes, Officer.

422
00:21:59,240 --> 00:22:00,810
They are both college students.

423
00:22:00,810 --> 00:22:03,010
This won't really affect them, will it?

424
00:22:03,100 --> 00:22:04,560
You guys can really fight,

425
00:22:04,940 --> 00:22:06,170
taking on so many people.

426
00:22:06,170 --> 00:22:06,680
[Police Office Operating Procedures]

427
00:22:06,680 --> 00:22:08,030
Does Huacheng University

428
00:22:08,030 --> 00:22:09,490
have a fighting major now?

429
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:12,110
They started it.

430
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:12,920
No matter who threw the first punch,

431
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:14,540
it's basically a brawl now.

432
00:22:15,310 --> 00:22:17,590
The bottle was about to hit her head.

433
00:22:17,590 --> 00:22:19,010
We couldn't just do nothing.

434
00:22:19,010 --> 00:22:19,280
[Duty Officer]

435
00:22:19,280 --> 00:22:21,070
You could have used reasonable defense,

436
00:22:21,070 --> 00:22:22,400
but you've gone...

437
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:23,310
Qin Wen.

438
00:22:23,310 --> 00:22:24,510
Come out for a second.

439
00:22:25,920 --> 00:22:26,790
Okay.

440
00:22:28,430 --> 00:22:29,680
[Police Office Operating Procedures]

441
00:22:29,680 --> 00:22:31,740
All of you, reflect on this properly.

442
00:22:43,450 --> 00:22:46,930
[Police-Civilian Joint Coordination Room]

443
00:22:49,680 --> 00:22:50,240
So?

444
00:22:50,750 --> 00:22:51,750
Have you decided?

445
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:56,760
What is there to think about?

446
00:22:57,310 --> 00:22:59,570
You're sure you won't reconcile, right?

447
00:23:00,640 --> 00:23:03,020
Just handle it according to the rules.

448
00:23:03,020 --> 00:23:04,850
[Police-Civilian Joint Coordination Room]

449
00:23:05,830 --> 00:23:06,720
Ma Kai, right?

450
00:23:07,790 --> 00:23:09,720
Why? Want to get to know me?

451
00:23:10,920 --> 00:23:12,000
I didn't bring my card today.

452
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:13,000
Maybe next time.

453
00:23:13,500 --> 00:23:15,390
Don't play the hooligan with me.

454
00:23:15,720 --> 00:23:16,230
Listen.

455
00:23:16,500 --> 00:23:17,310
I handle

456
00:23:17,350 --> 00:23:19,310
all the cases here impartially.

457
00:23:19,550 --> 00:23:20,960
No matter who it is,

458
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:22,110
if they break the law,

459
00:23:22,110 --> 00:23:23,750
I will treat them all the same.

460
00:23:23,750 --> 00:23:25,310
Everyone will be tried and sentenced
according to the law.

461
00:23:25,310 --> 00:23:26,710
You'll see that I mean it.

462
00:23:28,750 --> 00:23:29,750
What's your name?

463
00:23:31,440 --> 00:23:32,070
Qin Wen.

464
00:23:32,550 --> 00:23:34,080
Alright, I'll step closer.

465
00:23:35,480 --> 00:23:36,810
This is my badge number.

466
00:23:36,880 --> 00:23:37,590
Remember it.

467
00:23:37,590 --> 00:23:39,050
You'd better memorize it.

468
00:23:44,330 --> 00:23:45,310
[Mediation Center]

469
00:23:45,310 --> 00:23:47,240
All three of you, have you decided?

470
00:23:47,310 --> 00:23:50,070
Do you want to handle this
officially or privately?

471
00:23:50,070 --> 00:23:51,310
Officer,

472
00:23:51,740 --> 00:23:53,440
how are the injury
assessment results classified?

473
00:23:53,440 --> 00:23:54,030
Minor injury refers to

474
00:23:54,030 --> 00:23:56,270
moderate damage to a person's
limbs or appearance,

475
00:23:56,270 --> 00:23:57,240
or partial impairment

476
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:59,030
of hearing, vision,
or other organ functions.

477
00:23:59,030 --> 00:23:59,510
Serious injury

478
00:23:59,510 --> 00:24:01,920
refers to causing disability
of the limbs, disfigurement,

479
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:05,310
or complete loss of hearing, vision,
or other organ functions.

480
00:24:05,310 --> 00:24:07,200
Causing a minor injury
can result in up to three years'

481
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:08,640
imprisonment, detention,
or corrective measures.

482
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:09,920
Causing a serious injury
can result in a sentence

483
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:10,920
of three to ten years' imprisonment.

484
00:24:10,920 --> 00:24:11,640
Right?

485
00:24:13,020 --> 00:24:14,260
I study law.

486
00:24:15,640 --> 00:24:17,590
In that case,

487
00:24:19,880 --> 00:24:20,590
we

488
00:24:20,990 --> 00:24:22,520
won't settle it privately.

489
00:24:22,590 --> 00:24:24,520
We'll have the injuries assessed.

490
00:24:24,940 --> 00:24:26,180
Okay. Fine.

491
00:24:27,260 --> 00:24:27,980
Injury assessment?

492
00:24:27,980 --> 00:24:29,110
You want an assessment?

493
00:24:29,110 --> 00:24:30,240
Listen to me on this.

494
00:24:30,750 --> 00:24:30,840
I'll give you one.

495
00:24:30,840 --> 00:24:31,500
[Mediation Center]

496
00:24:31,500 --> 00:24:32,370
Get back!

497
00:24:33,070 --> 00:24:34,200
Who told you to move?

498
00:24:34,550 --> 00:24:35,550
Do you think this is a street market

499
00:24:35,550 --> 00:24:36,480
or something?

500
00:24:36,550 --> 00:24:36,580
And all of you, squat down!

501
00:24:36,580 --> 00:24:41,440
[Mediation Center]

502
00:24:41,440 --> 00:24:42,640
Squat down properly.

503
00:24:45,880 --> 00:24:48,180
Young Mr. Ma, it's all a misunderstanding.

504
00:24:48,180 --> 00:24:49,610
Please, don't hold it against us.

505
00:24:49,610 --> 00:24:51,030
Let's just forget about it, alright?

506
00:24:51,030 --> 00:24:52,230
I know what I'm doing.

507
00:24:52,280 --> 00:24:53,040
Fine.

508
00:24:54,550 --> 00:24:56,110
I'll do you this favor.

509
00:24:56,110 --> 00:24:56,870
[Police-Civilian Joint Coordination Room]

510
00:24:56,870 --> 00:24:58,070
Since we're friends,

511
00:24:58,680 --> 00:25:00,160
let's call this done.

512
00:25:04,350 --> 00:25:06,250
This cop's got some spunk.

513
00:25:06,300 --> 00:25:08,690
It's the first time anyone's
ever talked to me like that.

514
00:25:08,690 --> 00:25:09,070
Kai.

515
00:25:09,680 --> 00:25:11,070
Why bother with her?

516
00:25:11,160 --> 00:25:12,350
She's nothing.

517
00:25:16,860 --> 00:25:18,430
Give me a smoke.

518
00:25:19,830 --> 00:25:20,510
Kai.

519
00:25:27,070 --> 00:25:27,640
Lin Hua.

520
00:25:28,740 --> 00:25:29,500
Young Mr. Ma.

521
00:25:33,810 --> 00:25:36,030
Your two friends are really something.

522
00:25:36,090 --> 00:25:37,090
So loyal.

523
00:25:40,380 --> 00:25:42,520
But when they go off to university,

524
00:25:43,330 --> 00:25:44,780
you'll still be here.

525
00:25:45,790 --> 00:25:47,520
We've got plenty of time ahead.

526
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:53,710
Ma Kai, that's enough.

527
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:56,160
Don't burn your bridges.

528
00:25:56,790 --> 00:25:58,160
What did you say?

529
00:25:58,400 --> 00:25:59,030
What are you doing?

530
00:25:59,030 --> 00:26:00,560
This is the police station.

531
00:26:12,110 --> 00:26:13,110
Just wait and see.

532
00:26:15,180 --> 00:26:16,010
Be careful.

533
00:26:19,750 --> 00:26:20,850
What a bad day.

534
00:26:21,240 --> 00:26:22,880
We ran into something like this.

535
00:26:22,880 --> 00:26:25,070
You shouldn't have apologized to him.

536
00:26:25,440 --> 00:26:26,270
It's okay.

537
00:26:26,270 --> 00:26:28,070
A wise man knows when to retreat.

538
00:26:28,240 --> 00:26:29,110
Lin Hua.

539
00:26:29,110 --> 00:26:31,370
It's pitch dark. Where are you taking us?

540
00:26:31,650 --> 00:26:33,310
You'll know when we get there.

541
00:26:34,050 --> 00:26:36,650
Isn't this that junk plane
we played on as kids?

542
00:26:36,880 --> 00:26:39,460
It's not junk anymore.

543
00:26:40,270 --> 00:26:42,270
Lin Hua, why do you bring us here?

544
00:26:43,270 --> 00:26:44,110
Just follow me.

545
00:26:44,110 --> 00:26:44,680
So scary.

546
00:26:45,550 --> 00:26:46,680
Tonight,

547
00:26:46,750 --> 00:26:48,590
you two can stay here for the night.

548
00:26:48,590 --> 00:26:49,830
Wait, stay here?

549
00:26:50,350 --> 00:26:51,550
Go up and have a look.

550
00:26:53,030 --> 00:26:53,830
Hurry up.

551
00:26:53,830 --> 00:26:54,590
Will this work?

552
00:26:54,590 --> 00:26:56,070
There's no one else.

553
00:26:57,010 --> 00:26:58,440
Why am I so scared?

554
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:00,180
I'll go check it out first.

555
00:27:16,440 --> 00:27:17,110
How is it?

556
00:27:19,790 --> 00:27:21,720
Not bad.

557
00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:23,510
You've really kept this place nice.

558
00:27:23,510 --> 00:27:25,070
It's okay.

559
00:27:25,320 --> 00:27:28,000
You haven't been back much
over the past few years at university,

560
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:29,790
so I've been tidying it up bit by bit.

561
00:27:29,790 --> 00:27:31,590
Whenever I miss you, I come here.

562
00:27:32,150 --> 00:27:33,590
Forever friends.

563
00:27:33,680 --> 00:27:35,280
Lu Ming, Xia Xue, and Lin Hua.

564
00:27:35,440 --> 00:27:36,900
The words are still there.

565
00:27:37,790 --> 00:27:39,400
Did it cost you a lot
to get this place looking like this?

566
00:27:39,400 --> 00:27:40,400
Not really.

567
00:27:40,510 --> 00:27:41,640
I gathered

568
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:42,440
a lot of stuff.

569
00:27:42,440 --> 00:27:44,970
And for some things,
I just fixed them myself.

570
00:27:50,550 --> 00:27:51,740
Listen to this record
the moment you get back?

571
00:27:51,740 --> 00:27:53,160
Don't you ever get tired of it?

572
00:27:53,160 --> 00:27:55,830
My dad drinks with your dad every day,
and he never gets tired of it.

573
00:27:55,830 --> 00:27:58,490
Just like I never get tired
of drinking with you.

574
00:27:58,750 --> 00:28:00,240
You've finally come back.

575
00:28:00,240 --> 00:28:00,880
Come on.

576
00:28:01,270 --> 00:28:01,960
Cheers.

577
00:28:02,130 --> 00:28:03,120
Don't say that.

578
00:28:03,350 --> 00:28:05,770
After this summer break,
we'll start our internships.

579
00:28:05,770 --> 00:28:07,550
Then we'll come back
and drink together every day.

580
00:28:07,550 --> 00:28:08,640
♪ But my heart skips a beat,
I'm lost in this dream of youth ♪

581
00:28:08,640 --> 00:28:09,920
I'll drink you under the table.

582
00:28:09,920 --> 00:28:10,880
Come on.

583
00:28:12,950 --> 00:28:17,130
♪ Oh, my first love,
I tremble inside as I plead ♪

584
00:28:18,520 --> 00:28:22,380
♪ Are you the one
who belongs only to me? ♪

585
00:28:23,530 --> 00:28:27,210
♪ I'm afraid to say it,
and afraid you'll know ♪

586
00:28:28,510 --> 00:28:33,350
♪ I just hope you'll catch me
if I gather the courage to run to you ♪

587
00:28:36,720 --> 00:28:37,650
I'm heading off.

588
00:28:39,310 --> 00:28:40,440
Where are you going?

589
00:28:41,310 --> 00:28:42,640
Home.

590
00:28:42,720 --> 00:28:44,650
I'll leave you two some time alone.

591
00:28:44,820 --> 00:28:45,440
Lin Hua.

592
00:28:47,720 --> 00:28:48,590
I think

593
00:28:48,920 --> 00:28:50,520
what you said at dinner today

594
00:28:51,070 --> 00:28:52,350
was absolutely right.

595
00:28:55,160 --> 00:28:56,350
What did I say?

596
00:28:57,830 --> 00:28:58,960
What a pity.

597
00:28:59,440 --> 00:29:00,750
We've just got back,

598
00:29:00,750 --> 00:29:01,880
and the summer break's only just started.

599
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:03,200
Why are you sighing?

600
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:04,780
I mean,

601
00:29:05,110 --> 00:29:06,920
I still have to wait two years

602
00:29:06,920 --> 00:29:09,110
before I can attend your wedding.

603
00:29:09,110 --> 00:29:10,680
We never said

604
00:29:10,680 --> 00:29:12,880
we'd get married right after graduation.

605
00:29:12,880 --> 00:29:14,030
Uncle Xia already approves.

606
00:29:14,030 --> 00:29:15,560
So why not seize the moment?

607
00:29:15,720 --> 00:29:17,550
The new millennium is coming.

608
00:29:17,550 --> 00:29:18,790
What a great date,

609
00:29:18,790 --> 00:29:20,850
a truly once-in-a-lifetime moment.

610
00:29:21,240 --> 00:29:22,920
Why don't you two register first

611
00:29:22,920 --> 00:29:24,450
and hold the wedding later?

612
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:30,110
What am I waiting for?

613
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:32,920
I won't wait.

614
00:29:35,030 --> 00:29:36,200
What are you talking about?

615
00:29:36,200 --> 00:29:37,270
Are you drunk?

616
00:29:38,310 --> 00:29:39,070
I'm leaving.

617
00:29:44,550 --> 00:29:45,280
I'm leaving.

618
00:29:45,310 --> 00:29:45,960
Xia Xue.

619
00:29:46,590 --> 00:29:47,450
I'm going home.

620
00:29:47,750 --> 00:29:49,150
You're leaving already?

621
00:29:49,440 --> 00:29:50,770
I want to propose to her.

622
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:13,030
Kai.

623
00:30:14,430 --> 00:30:15,290
How about this?

624
00:30:15,790 --> 00:30:16,920
I'll bring that cop

625
00:30:17,480 --> 00:30:19,210
and those three scumbags to you

626
00:30:19,820 --> 00:30:21,080
and let you beat them up

627
00:30:21,510 --> 00:30:22,910
to vent some anger. Okay?

628
00:30:23,480 --> 00:30:24,030
Go ahead.

629
00:30:27,240 --> 00:30:27,880
Kai.

630
00:30:29,480 --> 00:30:31,440
Master's already angry.

631
00:30:32,470 --> 00:30:34,980
We can't go too far, right?

632
00:30:35,120 --> 00:30:35,850
How about...

633
00:30:37,860 --> 00:30:38,720
How about this?

634
00:30:39,830 --> 00:30:41,860
Give it a couple of days
till Master cools down,

635
00:30:41,860 --> 00:30:44,130
I'll have the guys sack them up,

636
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:45,680
and you can give them

637
00:30:45,680 --> 00:30:47,200
a good beating to vent your anger.

638
00:30:47,200 --> 00:30:47,930
Is that okay?

639
00:30:52,140 --> 00:30:55,940
[Maintain a safe speed.
Navigate with caution]

640
00:30:59,400 --> 00:31:00,160
Xia.

641
00:31:01,840 --> 00:31:02,510
Chief.

642
00:31:02,920 --> 00:31:04,920
The fire department sent down
a batch of equipment.

643
00:31:04,920 --> 00:31:05,650
Go around

644
00:31:05,680 --> 00:31:06,480
and distribute it

645
00:31:06,480 --> 00:31:07,730
to each department.

646
00:31:07,760 --> 00:31:08,850
Sure, no problem.

647
00:31:09,220 --> 00:31:10,930
Hey, Liu, come with me.

648
00:31:10,950 --> 00:31:11,400
Okay.

649
00:31:11,920 --> 00:31:12,830
Just you.

650
00:31:14,930 --> 00:31:16,830
Just me?

651
00:31:26,460 --> 00:31:27,320
The higher-ups

652
00:31:27,650 --> 00:31:29,170
specifically asked

653
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:30,590
for you, Xia Gang, to do it.

654
00:31:30,590 --> 00:31:31,650
They also said that

655
00:31:31,850 --> 00:31:32,640
if you

656
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:34,170
are too old to do it anymore,

657
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:38,360
I should find someone younger
to replace you.

658
00:31:55,400 --> 00:31:56,830
Who is Jianjun?

659
00:31:59,370 --> 00:32:00,210
I am.

660
00:32:04,690 --> 00:32:06,890
So you're the police officer's family?

661
00:32:07,110 --> 00:32:09,890
Officer Qin cooked this meal for you?

662
00:32:12,430 --> 00:32:14,430
Is there something you need, Mr. Ma?

663
00:32:15,720 --> 00:32:17,350
How do you put up

664
00:32:17,350 --> 00:32:19,060
with a shrew at home?

665
00:32:20,830 --> 00:32:21,880
Watch your words.

666
00:32:22,870 --> 00:32:24,200
Getting angry already?

667
00:32:25,410 --> 00:32:27,470
You still need to work on your temper.

668
00:32:29,030 --> 00:32:30,430
If there's nothing else,

669
00:32:30,480 --> 00:32:31,460
I'm going to eat.

670
00:32:33,200 --> 00:32:35,260
Mr. Xia, your stamina's impressive.

671
00:32:38,240 --> 00:32:39,110
Mr. Ma said that

672
00:32:40,110 --> 00:32:41,160
these fire extinguishers

673
00:32:41,160 --> 00:32:42,530
must be distributed today,

674
00:32:42,530 --> 00:32:45,260
or it'll hold up
the departments' replacements.

675
00:32:45,680 --> 00:32:47,140
If you don't finish today,

676
00:32:48,480 --> 00:32:50,210
you might be off duty tomorrow.

677
00:32:50,960 --> 00:32:52,070
I'm not making this up.

678
00:32:52,070 --> 00:32:53,310
Mr. Ma said it.

679
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:58,680
I just want you to pass
a message to Officer Qin.

680
00:32:59,640 --> 00:33:01,800
I'll take good care of you.

681
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:12,110
Sorry, Mr. Xia.

682
00:33:12,110 --> 00:33:12,790
Sorry, I'm sorry.

683
00:33:12,790 --> 00:33:13,750
I'm leaving now.

684
00:33:14,640 --> 00:33:16,440
Xia Gang. Off duty.

685
00:33:16,730 --> 00:33:17,910
It even rhymes.

686
00:33:18,880 --> 00:33:21,340
Blame your own bad luck for that.

687
00:34:58,150 --> 00:34:59,180
Let me sleep a bit longer.

688
00:34:59,180 --> 00:35:00,310
Come on.

689
00:35:00,880 --> 00:35:01,280
I'm not awake yet.

690
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:02,800
Get up quickly.

691
00:35:03,230 --> 00:35:04,550
Get up.

692
00:35:13,960 --> 00:35:16,190
What else should we buy
to bring back for Mom?

693
00:35:16,190 --> 00:35:17,000
Let's see.

694
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:18,330
I'll get you some fruit.

695
00:35:18,720 --> 00:35:19,960
These kumquats are nice.

696
00:35:19,960 --> 00:35:20,960
Two jin, please.

697
00:35:21,320 --> 00:35:22,190
Okay.

698
00:35:22,920 --> 00:35:25,000
Don't buy them. I told you already.

699
00:35:25,030 --> 00:35:26,290
I don't like kumquats.

700
00:35:26,510 --> 00:35:27,400
You have to eat some.

701
00:35:27,400 --> 00:35:28,660
How can you skip fruit?

702
00:35:28,760 --> 00:35:29,710
It helps cool you down.

703
00:35:29,710 --> 00:35:30,350
Here.

704
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:35,560
How do you know I've got a temper?

705
00:35:37,970 --> 00:35:39,380
I heard about Ma Kai.

706
00:35:41,950 --> 00:35:43,470
Did he give you trouble?

707
00:35:45,150 --> 00:35:46,110
No.

708
00:35:47,590 --> 00:35:48,480
Don't lie to me.

709
00:35:48,650 --> 00:35:50,580
If there's anything, just tell me.

710
00:35:52,070 --> 00:35:52,920
Don't worry.

711
00:35:53,060 --> 00:35:54,370
You've already taken the ring.

712
00:35:54,370 --> 00:35:55,390
We're family now.

713
00:35:57,550 --> 00:35:58,760
That's more like it.

714
00:36:00,230 --> 00:36:00,920
How much?

715
00:36:01,210 --> 00:36:02,210
Exactly ten yuan.

716
00:36:02,960 --> 00:36:03,980
Give it to me.

717
00:36:04,010 --> 00:36:04,670
Okay.

718
00:36:07,130 --> 00:36:07,940
Lin Hua.

719
00:36:08,960 --> 00:36:12,440
Do you know any jobs that pay daily?

720
00:36:18,230 --> 00:36:20,170
If I knew of any,
I'd be doing them myself.

721
00:36:20,170 --> 00:36:22,370
I'm not trying to borrow money from you.

722
00:36:24,650 --> 00:36:25,970
If you ask me,

723
00:36:26,880 --> 00:36:28,430
just buy a silver one.

724
00:36:28,710 --> 00:36:30,480
Xia Xue knows your situation.

725
00:36:30,480 --> 00:36:31,800
She won't mind.

726
00:36:32,070 --> 00:36:35,130
After you graduate,
you can save up and get a better one.

727
00:36:36,190 --> 00:36:38,990
Why didn't you just tell me
to twist one out of wire?

728
00:36:39,030 --> 00:36:40,490
Can I really skimp on this?

729
00:36:40,630 --> 00:36:41,570
Then what?

730
00:36:42,190 --> 00:36:44,160
Wait until you save enough to propose.

731
00:36:44,160 --> 00:36:45,020
That works too.

732
00:36:45,670 --> 00:36:46,940
Then buy a diamond ring.

733
00:36:46,940 --> 00:36:49,270
I heard big diamond rings
are in style now.

734
00:36:49,320 --> 00:36:50,280
They look great.

735
00:36:50,760 --> 00:36:51,880
A diamond ring?

736
00:36:51,960 --> 00:36:53,400
I can't even afford a gold one.

737
00:36:53,400 --> 00:36:54,440
There is gold.

738
00:36:57,030 --> 00:36:59,760
I heard there's some
placer gold over at Huijiang River.

739
00:36:59,760 --> 00:37:01,160
You could go pan for some.

740
00:37:01,280 --> 00:37:03,440
If you're lucky and strike a nugget,

741
00:37:03,630 --> 00:37:04,840
we've got the equipment in the workshop,

742
00:37:04,840 --> 00:37:05,840
I can make you one.

743
00:37:06,540 --> 00:37:08,750
A big gold ring.

744
00:37:11,760 --> 00:37:14,020
Can we still get into the workshop today?

745
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:15,630
Sure.

746
00:37:15,800 --> 00:37:16,470
Why?

747
00:37:32,670 --> 00:37:33,610
Where did you go?

748
00:37:34,110 --> 00:37:35,000
Look at this.

749
00:37:37,030 --> 00:37:38,130
What is it?

750
00:37:40,190 --> 00:37:41,380
Gold?

751
00:37:42,570 --> 00:37:43,700
Where did you get it?

752
00:37:50,480 --> 00:37:51,000
Mom!

753
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:54,800
Where did you put the longevity lock
my grandma gave me?

754
00:37:54,800 --> 00:37:56,030
The left drawer.

755
00:37:56,070 --> 00:37:57,880
The first one. See if it's there.

756
00:37:58,750 --> 00:37:59,800
Found it.

757
00:38:02,300 --> 00:38:03,500
I've made up my mind.

758
00:38:03,590 --> 00:38:04,800
Since I can't give her the best,

759
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:05,800
I'll make her

760
00:38:05,800 --> 00:38:07,400
the most special one myself.

761
00:38:07,400 --> 00:38:08,860
You silly thing. Alright.

762
00:38:16,880 --> 00:38:18,230
It looks like its shape has changed a bit.

763
00:38:18,230 --> 00:38:18,630
Right.

764
00:38:19,510 --> 00:38:20,530
Almost there.

765
00:38:21,030 --> 00:38:22,490
That's it. That's the way.

766
00:38:29,230 --> 00:38:31,710
-You're talented.
-That's the way.

767
00:38:38,710 --> 00:38:39,480
Right.

768
00:38:48,040 --> 00:38:48,850
Try harder.

769
00:39:01,180 --> 00:39:02,530
That's it.

770
00:39:06,070 --> 00:39:07,070
Time flies,

771
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:08,800
and the years slip by.

772
00:39:09,410 --> 00:39:11,670
We've known each other for ten years now.

773
00:39:11,880 --> 00:39:13,740
In this fleeting stretch of time,

774
00:39:13,740 --> 00:39:15,710
you've given me endless warmth

775
00:39:16,230 --> 00:39:19,280
and made my life so much better.

776
00:39:19,760 --> 00:39:20,680
Hey, um...

777
00:39:21,440 --> 00:39:23,070
Lu Ming, let's take a break.

778
00:39:23,070 --> 00:39:23,840
It's already good enough.

779
00:39:23,840 --> 00:39:24,710
You've memorized it perfectly.

780
00:39:24,710 --> 00:39:25,880
Don't interrupt me.

781
00:39:26,190 --> 00:39:27,280
Let me practice a few more times.

782
00:39:27,280 --> 00:39:30,010
What if I get nervous
and forget my lines that day?

783
00:39:30,670 --> 00:39:32,110
That's enough.

784
00:39:32,510 --> 00:39:34,590
You've been saying it to me all day.

785
00:39:34,710 --> 00:39:36,240
I'm getting a bit sick of it.

786
00:39:36,320 --> 00:39:36,820
Wait.

787
00:39:36,940 --> 00:39:38,890
Why are you sick of it?

788
00:39:39,110 --> 00:39:40,440
If you want to practice,

789
00:39:41,070 --> 00:39:42,360
practice with that.

790
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:43,710
Just talk to the cow.

791
00:39:43,960 --> 00:39:44,840
I need to get home

792
00:39:44,840 --> 00:39:45,440
and fix the DV camera.

793
00:39:45,440 --> 00:39:46,320
Otherwise no one's gonna

794
00:39:46,320 --> 00:39:47,110
record your proposal.

795
00:39:47,110 --> 00:39:48,510
But I need human interaction.

796
00:39:48,510 --> 00:39:49,770
It's great. Keep it up.

797
00:39:50,400 --> 00:39:51,000
Keep it up!

798
00:40:01,550 --> 00:40:02,280
Cow!

799
00:40:03,360 --> 00:40:04,800
Listen up!

800
00:40:11,670 --> 00:40:12,360
What's up?

801
00:40:12,760 --> 00:40:13,690
Where is Lu Ming?

802
00:40:16,400 --> 00:40:17,360
He went home.

803
00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:19,030
Which home?

804
00:40:19,150 --> 00:40:20,070
Liar.

805
00:40:20,070 --> 00:40:21,280
I just came from home.

806
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:22,360
Tell me.

807
00:40:22,760 --> 00:40:24,360
What have you two been up to

808
00:40:24,380 --> 00:40:25,400
behind my back?

809
00:40:26,400 --> 00:40:27,190
Nothing.

810
00:40:27,190 --> 00:40:28,990
What could we possibly be doing?

811
00:40:30,880 --> 00:40:31,920
Time flies,

812
00:40:32,510 --> 00:40:33,760
and the years slip by.

813
00:40:34,920 --> 00:40:36,880
We've known each other for ten years now.

814
00:40:36,880 --> 00:40:38,810
This is him when he was
a hundred days old.

815
00:40:38,810 --> 00:40:39,710
Hundred days.

816
00:40:43,510 --> 00:40:44,480
Do you remember?

817
00:40:44,520 --> 00:40:46,880
He came first in his class
on his very first exam.

818
00:40:46,880 --> 00:40:49,320
I want to spend
the rest of my life with you.

819
00:40:49,960 --> 00:40:53,020
I wish for you to be my forever.

820
00:40:53,230 --> 00:40:54,510
He's been smart since he was little,

821
00:40:54,510 --> 00:40:55,800
with an especially good memory.

822
00:40:55,800 --> 00:40:57,530
In this... in this fleeting...

823
00:40:57,800 --> 00:40:59,630
In this fleeting stretch of time.

824
00:40:59,630 --> 00:41:01,710
Why can't I remember this line?

825
00:41:01,710 --> 00:41:02,640
He's meticulous

826
00:41:02,670 --> 00:41:03,960
and never scatterbrained.

827
00:41:03,960 --> 00:41:06,400
I've memorized it!

828
00:41:08,280 --> 00:41:10,410
This is you three having fun together.

829
00:41:10,840 --> 00:41:11,960
His physical condition

830
00:41:11,960 --> 00:41:13,220
is excellent—

831
00:41:13,550 --> 00:41:14,750
really coordinated.

832
00:41:17,440 --> 00:41:20,170
Even his teacher said
he was born to be an athlete.

833
00:41:21,630 --> 00:41:22,960
Anyway, being with him,

834
00:41:22,960 --> 00:41:24,880
you'll never regret it.

835
00:41:25,440 --> 00:41:27,100
I definitely won't regret it.

836
00:41:33,390 --> 00:41:36,130
You've made my life so much better.

837
00:41:40,520 --> 00:41:41,520
Today,

838
00:41:42,070 --> 00:41:42,440
I

839
00:41:43,110 --> 00:41:44,360
want to ask you,

840
00:41:44,360 --> 00:41:45,710
sincerely, to marry me.

841
00:41:52,530 --> 00:41:56,370
[2010]

842
00:42:05,920 --> 00:42:07,280
Here, have some water.

843
00:42:16,960 --> 00:42:18,210
Did you find

844
00:42:18,880 --> 00:42:21,080
that photo the police showed us that day

845
00:42:21,920 --> 00:42:22,920
a bit familiar?

846
00:42:24,950 --> 00:42:27,010
It kinda looks like him, but it's not.

847
00:42:29,710 --> 00:42:30,870
You've met already?

848
00:42:35,190 --> 00:42:36,990
I don't mean anything else by it.

849
00:42:37,590 --> 00:42:38,920
I'm just a bit worried.

850
00:42:40,480 --> 00:42:41,590
If this really has

